label.value: Carnitine Acetyl Transferase Measurement

value.value: The determination of the amount of carnitine Acetyl transferase present in a sample.

label.value: Cholinesterase Measurement

value.value: The determination of the amount of cholinesterase present in a sample.

label.value: Systemic Disease

value.value: A clinical course finding indicating that a disease presents with systemic manifestations.

label.value: Cystatin C Measurement

value.value: The determination of the amount of cystatin C present in a sample.

label.value: Monoclonal Protein Measurement

value.value: The determination of the amount of monoclonal protein present in a sample.

label.value: Tryptase Measurement

value.value: The determination of the amount of tryptase present in a sample.

label.value: Apolipoprotein E4 Measurement

value.value: The determination of the amount of apolipoprotein E4 present in a sample.

label.value: Beta Globulin to Total Protein Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of beta globulin compared to total protein present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: Gamma Globulin to Total Protein Ratio Measurement

value.value: The determination of the ratio of gamma globulin compared to total protein present in a sample. The measurement may be expressed as a ratio or percentage.

label.value: Erythrocyte Cell Morphology

value.value: An examination or assessment of the form and structure of red blood cells.

label.value: Leukocyte Cell Morphology

value.value: An examination or assessment of the form and structure of white blood cells.

label.value: Neisseria gonorrhoeae Measurement

value.value: The determination of the amount of Neisseria gonorrhoeae present in a sample.

label.value: Alcian Blue Staining Method

value.value: A microscopy staining method that utilizes alcian blue, a cationic, water soluble copper-containing phthalocyanine dye to determine the presence of acid mucopolysaccharides and glycosaminoglycans.

label.value: Vaccine

value.value: Preparations containing substances with antigenic properties administered to activate the immune system, thereby inducing an immune response.

label.value: Myelosuppression

value.value: A laboratory test result indicating low production of erythrocytes, leukocytes and/or thrombocytes from the bone marrow.

label.value: Luxol Fast Blue and Cresyl Violet Staining Method

value.value: A microscopy staining method that utilizes luxol fast blue, an alcohol soluble copper phthalocyanine dye, and cresyl violet, an organic compound that is commonly used as a counter stain, to determine the presence of myelin as well as helicobacter and campylobacter bacterial species.

label.value: Lead Citrate Staining Method

value.value: A microscopy staining method that utilizes lead citrate, a mixture of lead nitrate and sodium citrate, and has applications for electron microscopy staining.

label.value: Toluidine Blue Staining Method

value.value: A microscopy staining method that utilizes toluidine blue, a solution composed of tolonium chloride, to determine the presence of mast cells, lignin, proteoglycans and glycosaminoglycans.

label.value: Uranyl Acetate Staining Method

value.value: A microscopy staining method that utilizes uranyl acetate, a water insoluble yellow crystalline solid, which is used as a negative stain in electron microscopy.

label.value: Alcian Blue and Periodic Acid Schiff Staining Method

value.value: A microscopy staining method that utilizes periodic acid, an oxoacid of iodine, Schiff reagent, the reaction product of fuchsine and sodium bisulfite, and Alcian blue, a water soluble copper phthalocyanine dye. This staining method is used to differentially stain glycoproteins.

label.value: AUC Dosing to Last Concentration Normalized by Weight

value.value: The area under the curve (AUC) from the time of dosing to the last measurable concentration divided by the weight.

label.value: AUC All Normalized by Dose

value.value: The area under the curve (AUC) from the time of dosing to the time of the last observation divided by the dose, regardless of whether the last concentration is measurable or not.

label.value: AUC All Normalized by Surface Area

value.value: The area under the curve (AUC) from the time of dosing to the time of the last observation divided by the surface area, regardless of whether the last concentration is measurable or not.

label.value: AUC All Normalized by Weight

value.value: The area under the curve (AUC) from the time of dosing to the time of the last observation divided by the weight, regardless of whether the last concentration is measurable or not.

label.value: AUC Dosing to Last Concentration Normalized by Body Mass Index

value.value: The area under the curve (AUC) from the time of dosing to the last measurable concentration divided by the body mass index.

label.value: Merkel Cell Carcinoma

value.value: A rare aggressive neuroendocrine carcinoma that usually arises from the skin. Rarely, it arises from extracutaneous sites, including the oral cavity, salivary glands, breast, vulva, and vaginal wall. The tumor is composed of small round cells with scanty cytoplasm. Merkel cell polyomavirus is implicated in the majority of cases.

label.value: AUC Infinity Observed Normalized by Surface Area

value.value: The observed area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity divided by the surface area.

label.value: AUC Infinity Observed Normalized by Weight

value.value: The observed area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity divided by the weight.

label.value: AUC Infinity Predicted Normalized by Body Mass Index

value.value: The area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity from dosing time, based on the predicted last concentration, divided by the body mass index.

label.value: Weight Change

value.value: The area under the curve (AUC) for the defined interval between doses (TAU) divided by the dose.

label.value: AUMC Dosing to Last Concentration Normalized by Body Mass Index

value.value: The area under the moment curve (AUMC) from the time of dosing to the last measurable concentration divided by the body mass index.

label.value: Juvenile Myelomonocytic Leukemia

value.value: A clonal myeloid disorder of childhood previously classified as myelodysplastic/myeloproliferative neoplasm. It is characterized by the presence of monocytic proliferation in peripheral blood, less than 20% blasts in bone marrow and peripheral blood, splenomegaly, and the absence of BCR-ABL1 fusion. Almost all patients carry mutations of the RAS pathway.

label.value: AUMC Infinity Observed Normalized by Body Mass Index

label.value: AUMC Infinity Observed Normalized by Dose

value.value: The area under the first moment curve (AUMC) extrapolated to infinity, based on the last observed concentration divided by the dose.
